Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.73,0:00:07.22,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Aunque la historia de Hanekawa Tsubasa es mi historia, no es una que pueda contar.{Though the tale of Tsubasa Hanekawa is my tale, \Nit is not one that I can tell.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.24,0:00:15.74,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Eso es porque ni siquiera puedo definir hasta qué punto soy yo. {That’s because I can’t even define \Nthe extent to which I am me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.74,0:00:19.99,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Creo que una vez, hubo un gran autor que dijo que encontraba difícil de creerlo...{I believe there was once a great author \Nwho said he found it hard to believe that...}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.99,0:00:26.50,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...él mismo estaba hasta la punta de los pies extendidos, pero yo ni siquiera necesito extender mis piernas.{... he was himself down to the tips of his outstretched toes, \Nbut I don’t even need to extend my legs.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.50,0:00:31.80,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Es incierto si mi corazón es mío.{It’s uncertain whether my very heart is my own.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.80,0:00:34.18,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,¿Soy yo?{Am I me?}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.18,0:00:36.64,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,¿Que soy?{What am I?}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.64,0:00:39.22,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,¿Quién soy?{Who am I?}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.22,0:00:41.30,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,¿Quién─ soy yo?{Who─is me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.30,0:00:44.44,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,¿Qué─ soy yo?{What─is me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.44,0:00:49.06,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Por ejemplo, ¿de verdad podemos decir que yo soy estos pensamientos...{For example, could we really say \Nthat I am these thoughts...}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.06,0:00:52.02,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...que se consideran un sin sentido tan de cerca?{... that so closely consider this pointlessness?}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.02,0:00:55.78,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Quizás podamos decir eso, si solo fuéramos a decirlo.{Maybe we could say that, \Nif we’re only going to say it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.78,0:00:59.86,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Esos son solo sentimientos, pensamientos,{These are only feelings, thoughts,}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.86,0:01:03.28,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,e incluso, tal vez recuerdos,{and maybe even memories,}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.28,0:01:07.20,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,pero podríamos decir, que no son nada más que conocimiento acumulado.{but we might say that they’re nothing \Nmore than accumulated knowledge.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.20,0:01:09.54,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Si decimos que soy mis experiencias,{If we’re saying that I am my experiences,}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.54,0:01:12.96,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,¿eso significa que también podemos decir que un humano con las mismas experiencias mías...{does that mean we can also say a human \Nwith the exact same experiences as me...}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.96,0:01:17.42,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...en realidad podría ser yo?{... would actually be me?}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.42,0:01:21.72,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,¿Que podría existir un yo, diferente a mí, que aún fuera yo misma?{That there could be a me \Nother than me that was still me?}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.72,0:01:27.34,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,En ese caso, si yo fuera diferente de mi misma, ¿dejaría de ser yo?{In that case, if I were being unlike myself, \Nwould I no longer be me?}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.34,0:01:28.69,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,¿Qué pienso al respecto?,{What to think about that,}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.69,0:01:32.02,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,¿cómo me siento?{how to feel?}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.02,0:01:37.52,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Para comenzar, el nombre Hanekawa Tsubasa ya de por si es inestable.{To begin with, the name \NTsubasa Hanekawa is already unstable.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.52,0:01:40.62,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Mi apellido familiar ha cambiado varias veces.{My family name has changed a number of times.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.62,0:01:44.04,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Asi que no puedo buscar mi identidad por mi nombre,{So I can’t look for my identity in my name,}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.04,0:01:45.12,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,ni siquiera...{not even...}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.12,0:01:46.28,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...un poco.{... a bit.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.28,0:01:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.12,0:01:49.96,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Entiendo a un nivel muy profundo...{I understand on quite a deep-rooted level...}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.96,0:01:53.66,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...la idea de que los nombres no son más que significantes.{... the idea that names \Nare nothing more than signifiers.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.66,0:01:57.30,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Incluso podríamos decir que lo entiendo a un nivel corporal.{We could even say I understand \Nit on a bodily level.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.30,0:02:03.60,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Al enfrentar una excentricidad, nada es más importante que conocer su nombre─{In facing an aberration, \Nnothing is more important than knowing its name─}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.60,0:02:07.10,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,o al menos, eso se supone que sea el primer paso del proceso.{or at least, that’s supposed to \Nbe the first step in the process.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.10,0:02:12.02,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Asi que el hecho de que nunca reconociera mi nombre como propio...{So maybe the fact that I never \Nrecognized my name as my own...}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.02,0:02:18.36,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...era una razón principal del porque no me había enfrentado a mí misma.{... was a major reason I \Nhaven’t been facing myself.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.36,0:02:23.12,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,En ese caso, necesito comenzar a conocer mi nombre.{In that case, I need to begin by knowing my name.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.12,0:02:27.04,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Necesito conocer a Hanekawa Tsubasa como yo misma.{I need to know Tsubasa Hanekawa as myself.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.04,0:02:32.28,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Entonces quizás pueda definirme por primera vez a mí misma.{Then maybe I can define myself \Nfor the first time.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.28,0:02:38.72,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Por supuesto, cuando pienso en cómo es probable que Araragi-kun no se preocupe hasta la saciedad con esta clase de ideas, {Of course, when I think about how Araragi most likely doesn’t \Nworry himself into a standstill with these kinds of ideas,}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.72,0:02:43.96,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,mi estancamiento autoimpuesto aun me parece tonto y absurdo.{my self-imposed stalemate seems silly and absurd.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.96,0:02:45.50,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Él se puede convertir en un vampiro,{He can become a vampire,}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.50,0:02:47.76,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,perder su humanidad,{lose his humanity,}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.76,0:02:49.38,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,y ser arrastrado al otro mundo...{and be dragged into the other world...}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.38,0:02:52.48,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...por una multitud de excentricidades diferentes,{... by a host of different aberrations,}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.48,0:02:56.44,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,pero siempre seguirá siendo Araragi Koyomi,{but he always continues to be Koyomi Araragi,}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.44,0:02:57.94,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,con su inquebrantable ser,{with his unshakable self,}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.94,0:03:00.78,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,su inquebrantable ego, y me siento avergonzada...{his unshakable ego, and I feel embarrassed...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.78,0:03:03.86,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...cuando pienso en ello.{... when I think about that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.86,0:03:07.08,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Quizás él no se dé cuenta.{Maybe he doesn’t realize it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.08,0:03:09.12,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Es claro para todos alrededor de él,{It’s clear to anyone around him,}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.12,0:03:17.16,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,tan claro como el día, que él siempre continua siendo él mismo, sin importar la hora o el lugar,{as clear as day that he always continues \Nto be himself no matter the place or time,}
Comment: 0,0:03:09.12,0:03:11.92,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,as clear as day that he always continues \Nto be himself no matter the place or time,
Comment: 0,0:03:11.92,0:03:13.00,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,as clear as day that he always continues \Nto be himself no matter the place or time,
Comment: 0,0:03:13.00,0:03:14.38,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,as clear as day that he always continues \Nto be himself no matter the place or time,
Comment: 0,0:03:14.38,0:03:17.16,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,as clear as day that he always continues \Nto be himself no matter the place or time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.16,0:03:20.59,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,solo que tal vez, él no se haya dado cuenta.{but just maybe he doesn’t realize it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.59,0:03:22.50,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,No tiene porqué darse cuenta.{He doesn’t have to realize it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.50,0:03:27.64,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Araragi Koyomi puede ser Araragi Koyomi en confianza.{Koyomi Araragi can be \NKoyomi Araragi in confidence.}
Comment: 0,0:03:22.50,0:03:24.04,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Koyomi Araragi can be \NKoyomi Araragi in confidence.
Comment: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:25.54,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Koyomi Araragi can be \NKoyomi Araragi in confidence.
Comment: 0,0:03:25.55,0:03:27.64,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Koyomi Araragi can be \NKoyomi Araragi in confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.64,0:03:33.56,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Probablemente sea eso porqué él siempre pueda contar su propia historia.{That’s probably why he \Ncan always tell his own tale.}
Comment: 0,0:03:27.64,0:03:28.84,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,That’s probably why he \Ncan always tell his own tale.
Comment: 0,0:03:28.84,0:03:30.35,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,That’s probably why he \Ncan always tell his own tale.
Comment: 0,0:03:30.35,0:03:33.56,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,That’s probably why he \Ncan always tell his own tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.56,0:03:37.22,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Es por eso que lo amo.{That’s why I love him.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.22,0:03:38.90,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Hanekawa Tsubasa...{Tsubasa Hanekawa...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.90,0:03:42.06,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...ama a Araragi Koyomi.{... loves Koyomi Araragi.}
Comment: 0,0:03:38.90,0:03:39.98,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,... loves Koyomi Araragi.
Comment: 0,0:03:39.98,0:03:42.06,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,... loves Koyomi Araragi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.06,0:03:43.02,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Al final,{In the end,}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.02,0:03:48.08,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,cualquier yo con el que pueda hablar, tendría que comenzar por ahí.{any me I can speak \Nabout would have to begin there.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.08,0:03:50.54,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Curiosamente,{Amusingly enough,}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.54,0:03:53.00,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,eso es lo único seguro que hay en mí.{that is the only certain thing in me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:57.16,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Como cuando estoy estudiando sola en una mesa de la biblioteca...{Like when I’m studying alone \Nat a library desk...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.16,0:03:59.96,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...y de repente decida escribir mi nombre...{... and suddenly decide to write the name...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.96,0:04:01.30,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,"Araragi Tsubasa"{“Tsubasa Araragi”}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.30,0:04:05.38,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...en la esquina de mis notas y no pueda evitar sonreír.{... in the corner of my notes \Nand can’t help but smile.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.38,0:04:09.88,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Eso es todo lo que mi historia necesita ser.{That is all my tale needs to be.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.88,0:04:12.68,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,De todas las sesenta historias sobre las aventuras de Sherlock Holmes,{Of all sixty stories about \Nthe adventures of Sherlock Holmes,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.68,0:04:16.14,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,el famoso detective creado por Sir Arthur Conan Doyle,{the famed detective created \Nby Sir Arthur Conan Doyle,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.14,0:04:17.76,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,solo existen dos historias cortas...{only two shorts exist...}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.76,0:04:19.94,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...que no son narradas por su asistente, el Dr. Watson,{... that are narrated not \Nby his assistant, Dr. Watson,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.94,0:04:25.28,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,sino por el mismo Sherlock Holmes.{but by Sherlock Holmes himself.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.28,0:04:29.74,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Estas son obras polémicas entre los Sherlockianos, a veces incluso tratadas como apócrifas,{These are controversial works among Sherlockians, \Neven treated as apocryphal at times,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.74,0:04:33.32,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,pero en una de ellas, {\i1}"El soldado de la piel decolorada"{\i0},{but in one of them, \N“The Adventure of the Blanched Soldier,”}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.32,0:04:36.62,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Holmes comienza con estas palabras: {Mr. Holmes begins with these words:}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.62,0:04:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.90,0:04:42.59,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\i1}Las ideas de mi amigo Watson, aunque limitadas, \Nson extraordinariamente pertinaces.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.59,0:04:47.76,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\i1}Desde hace tiempo ha venido hostigándome\N para que escriba uno de mis casos.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.76,0:04:51.52,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\i1}Quizá he provocado yo mismo esa persecución,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.52,0:04:57.86,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\i1}por haberle hecho notar muchas veces\N la superficialidad de sus relatos...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.86,0:05:05.65,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\i1}...acusándole de inclinarse hacia el gusto popular, en vez de ceñirse rigurosamente a los hechos y a las cifras.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.65,0:05:07.41,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\i1}«¡Pruebe de escribir usted mismo, Holmes!»{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.41,0:05:08.90,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\i1}me ha solido replicar,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.90,0:05:11.33,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\i1}y ahora, después de tomar la pluma en la mano,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.33,0:05:13.74,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\i1}me veo forzado a reconocer que,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.74,0:05:20.08,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\i1}en efecto, empiezo a darme cuenta de que es preciso presentar el asunto de manera que pueda interesar al lector.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.08,0:05:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.80,0:05:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.17,0:05:25.84,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Como la mayoría, estaba fascinada por las habilidades casi sobrehumanas de Sherlock Holmes...{Like most, I was fascinated by \NSherlock Holmes’s near-superhuman abilities...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.84,0:05:29.54,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...mientras leía sus hazañas, por eso me sorprendió...{... as I read about his exploits, \Nwhich is why I was taken aback...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.54,0:05:34.56,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...cuando abruptamente le dio voz a esos "verdaderos sentimientos".{... when he abruptly gave voice \Nto these “true feelings.”}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.56,0:05:37.80,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Para ser franca, estaba decepcionada.{To be frank, I was disappointed.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.80,0:05:40.69,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,¿Por qué este hombre, que había hecho una muestra extraordinaria tras otra...{Why would this man who had made one \Nextraordinary display after another...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.69,0:05:44.10,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...ahora había elegido decir algo tan humano?{... now choose to say such a human thing?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.10,0:05:47.44,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Me sentí traicionada.{I felt betrayed.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.44,0:05:48.52,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Pero...{But...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.52,0:05:50.70,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...ahora lo entiendo.{... now I understand.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.70,0:05:53.78,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Entiendo su humanidad, la cual ya no...{I understand his humanity, \Nwhich could no longer...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.78,0:05:55.70,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...soporta la brecha entre él...{... bear the gap between him...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.70,0:05:59.66,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,...como el "superman" hablado por el Dr. Watson, y el él de si mismo.{... as the “superman” spoken \Nof by Dr. Watson, and him as himself.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.66,0:06:03.74,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,Sus sentimientos de querer excusarse.{His feelings of wanting \Nto make an excuse for himself.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.74,0:06:04.67,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,En definitiva,{Ultimately,}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.67,0:06:09.96,Hanekawa,,0,0,0,,estas dos historias están posicionadas como el resultado del asistente de un detective reconocido que le contesta:  {those two stories are positioned as the outcome \Nof a renowned detective’s assistant talking back to him:}
